    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1106.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 24, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your despatch of the 8th of September, No. 780, which is accompanied by a copy
                    of a correspondence between yourself and Earl Russell in regard to the capture
                    of the Georgia, and in which his lordship desires that the case may be brought
                    before a prize court <pb facs="0330" n="310" xml:id="pg_310"/> for adjudication
                    as soon as possible. In reply, I have to inform you that the proceedings in the
                    case will be regular, and attended by no unnecessary delay.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
